President Donald J. Trump has announced that Anthony Scaramucci, a successful entrepreneur and founder of SkyBridge Capital, will be appointed as the White House Communications Director. Scaramucci will be responsible for overseeing the entire communications operation, including message development and strategy, and will report directly to the President. Trump praised Scaramucci's support and stated that he will help implement key aspects of the administration's agenda. Scaramucci expressed his pride in joining the administration and highlighted Trump's accomplishments in a short period of time. Currently serving as the senior vice president and chief strategy officer at the Export-Import Bank, Scaramucci will officially assume his new role on August 15, 2017.